HEADWORD: Pontine
<hw>Pon"tine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Pontinus</ets> or <ets>Pomptinus</ets>, an appellation given to a
district in Latium, near <ets>Pometia</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of or
pertaining to an extensive marshy district between Rome and
Naples.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>Pomptine</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pontlevis</ent>⟦br⟧
